### Definitions for Evaluating Forgetting

We measure the phenomenon of model forgetting by reusing an in-context example within \(\{\bm{x}_{i},y_{i}\}_{i=1}^{n}\) as the test example \(\bm{x}_{\mathrm{test}}\). In experiments of Figure 5, we fix \(n=20\) and reuse \(\bm{x}_{\mathrm{test}}=\bm{x}_{i}\). We denote the "Time Stamp Gap" as the distance the reused example index \(i\) from the current time stamp \(n=20\). We measure the forgetting of index \(i\) as

\[\mathrm{Forgetting}(\mathcal{A},i)=\mathop{\mathbb{E}}_{\{\bm{x}_{i},y_{i}\}_ {i=1}^{n}\sim P_{\mathrm{D}}}\mathrm{MSE}\Big{(}\mathcal{A}(\bm{x}_{i}\mid\{ \bm{x}_{i},y_{i}\}_{i=1}^{n}),y_{i}\Big{)}\] (17)

Note: the further away \(i\) is from \(n\), the more possible algorithm \(\mathcal{A}\) forgets.

